fields.Title: Rhetoric: "You're pretty sure you can live in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're pretty sure you can live in a tree elsewhere too -- but he wouldn't believe it anyway.

fields.Title: You: "No use prying."
fields.Dialogue Text: No use prying.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh... I like expeditions, and I li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh... I like expeditions, and I like you. I can give you..." He counts in his head. "... 10 reál."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Fair point," he agrees, "You can't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fair point," he agrees, "You can't have a successful business without a loyal customer base. How much is your loyalty worth?"

fields.Title: You: ""Ten reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ten reál."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Shush, please..." He looks around,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shush, please..." He looks around, then lowers his voice. "There's *bad* people doing *bad* things here -- that's all I know. Please don't get me into this mess, I've spent *fifteen* years working my way up..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Who *exactly* is talking about thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who *exactly* is talking about this lady-driver of yours? The racist? Or the other one, with the tattoos?" He points north.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Tapes, you mean like music tapes?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tapes, you mean like music tapes? No, music is *out*! Don't listen to music. I sell extremely cool sunglasses if you want get your *mojo* going." He points at the shoddy box on the left.

fields.Title: You: ""Alright, so you have no idea whats..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, so you have no idea whatsoever where I could find tapes?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The *Apricot Suzerainty*," the lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The *Apricot Suzerainty*," the lieutenant explains, "is what the Siigay archipelago is commonly known as in Revachol." He pauses. "It's a bit of a *fraught* term, I'm sure you understand."

fields.Title: You: ""Just kidding. I'm really here to s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just kidding. I'm really here to shake you down for some *answers* to official police questions."

fields.Title: You: ""Right, but isn't it only a shithol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right, but isn't it only a shithole *because* of Revachol?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh! Oh no! It's very simple, actua..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh! Oh no! It's very simple, actually. Siigay is a shithole. Not good for independent entrepreneurs like this one here. That's why I came to Revachol."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Siileng: ""You're right, officer, 100%." He r..."]
You: ""What kind of stuff are you selling..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What kind of stuff are you selling here?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Siigay, Apricot Suzerainty -- it's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Siigay, Apricot Suzerainty -- it's all the same to me, it's all cool. I'm interested in sales. Go ahead, let's make one." He gestures to the boxes. "Super high quality, friendly prices."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No-no, apricots come from Siigay,"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no, apricots come from Siigay," the vendor explains. "My grandma used to grow them. But Siigay is a shithole, that's why I came to Revachol. Here's much better for an independent entrepreneur. Less *laws*."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Ah, yes. Money is very important."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, yes. Money is very important." The street vendor nods, dead-serious.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm *not* gonna confiscate this hu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm *not* gonna confiscate this humanitarian aid that you're reselling."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm *not* going tell HUMANOX about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm *not* going tell HUMANOX about the little side business you've got here."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Officer, do I look like *I* have t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, do I look like *I* have that kinda money? Be reasonable."

fields.Title: You: ""One million reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "One million reál."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""It's a *she*, okay?" he whispers...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a *she*, okay?" he whispers. "The other drivers call her the *lady driver*. You're better off staying away from her -- the way they talk about her..." He shakes his head. "She's no lady."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A lady driver? Perhaps connected to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A lady driver? Perhaps connected to *Ruby* somehow?

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I don't know... I'm not local. I d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know... I'm not local. I don't know anything about that."

fields.Title: You: ""So... where are you from?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So... where are you from?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Me? It's a boring story, officer...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Me? It's a boring story, officer. Who cares about the past? I'm all business now -- all Revachol."

fields.Title: Siileng: "He raises his arms in mock alarm. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He raises his arms in mock alarm. "Don't shoot, officer! Have we got an arrest here, or just a shakedown?"

fields.Title: You: ""This isn't a joke. Give me your mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This isn't a joke. Give me your money. I need money."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""A cop limping down the street, ble..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A cop limping down the street, bleeding from the shoulder, face bruised, looking like hell... You know what that is?"

fields.Title: You: ""But you're a foreigner. I'm protec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you're a foreigner. I'm protecting the business interests of foreign nations!"

fields.Title: You: ""Doesn't that beat the idea of huma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't that beat the idea of humanitarian aid? It's *supposed* to be free. That's what makes it humanitarian."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "We'll need more if we're going to p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We'll need more if we're going to pin this one down, he thinks -- good questions, though. Sharp eyes, officer.

fields.Title: You: "Persuade him to give you some money..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Persuade him to give you some money.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Alright, this should help you get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright, this should help you get back on your feet." He takes a ten-note from a leather pouch.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't even want happiness, or *u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't even want happiness, or *un-unhappiness* -- I just don't want to die."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "After all this mess -- the broken s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: After all this mess -- the broken seals, lying to you? C'mon!

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's *even* cooler -- you invest..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's *even* cooler -- you investigating narcotics crimes like that. But --" he points to the goods. "I am not a lorry driver, I'm just a street vendor. I don't know anything about that."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No! I just said I work harder and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No! I just said I work harder and he's an asshole. I'm..." He stops to think.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Realizing he can't get out of it. S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Realizing he can't get out of it. Smart man.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what crowd?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what crowd?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""All of them, I don't know. I told..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All of them, I don't know. I told you all I know. Are we cool now? I really want us to be cool now."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I don't know... maybe? If she is,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know... maybe? If she is, I haven't gone near her. I don't get *involved*, I told you."

fields.Title: You: ""Hey, you seem like a really succes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, you seem like a really successful entrepreneur... would you like to support a member of the local police force?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""... you're *very* cool." He makes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... you're *very* cool." He makes both hands into finger-pistols and fires a few finger-bullets into the air.

fields.Title: You: ""You're from the 'Apricot Suzeraint..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're from the 'Apricot Suzerainty', right?"

fields.Title: You: ""Why's it called that? Lots of apri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why's it called that? Lots of apricots there?"

fields.Title: You: ""This isn't a joke. Give me your mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This isn't a joke. Give me your money. I need money."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Of course, I'll come quietly." A s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course, I'll come quietly." A sly wink. "But perhaps I could convince you to arrest some of my wares, officer? With your money, maybe?"

fields.Title: You: "(Wince.) "Isn't that name kind of....."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Wince.) "Isn't that name kind of... insensitive?"

fields.Title: Logic: "No, it's still Ruby. Interesting th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it's still Ruby. Interesting that he doesn't seem aware of her existence, though...

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Cool. That's *cool*." He nods and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool. That's *cool*." He nods and settles back into the pile of boxes.

fields.Title: Empathy: "The air between you becomes a littl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air between you becomes a little awkward as it becomes clear you don't know the first thing about bribes.

fields.Title: Drama: "A blatant lie, sire. Yet he tells i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A blatant lie, sire. Yet he tells it with such conviction. We'd believe him -- if we didn't know better.

fields.Title: You: ""Who are you afraid of, Siileng?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who are you afraid of, Siileng?"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay. If you don't know then I'll..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. If you don't know then I'll tell your employer you've been selling his stuff."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Okay, look..." The vendor looks ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, look..." The vendor looks around, then lowers his voice. "There's *bad* people doing *bad* things here -- that's all I know. Please don't get me into this mess, I've spent *fifteen* years working my way up..."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""All of them. Even the ones who've..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All of them. Even the ones who've left. I don't hang out with them, I don't remember who has tattoos."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""There's one by the statue of that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's one by the statue of that king." He points towards the roundabout. "I haven't gone near her. And I *won't* either."

fields.Title: You: ""Nah, it's not code. I really mean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, it's not code. I really mean my individual net worth."

fields.Title: Siileng: "He nods at the empty lorry cabin be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods at the empty lorry cabin behind his back. "No one would ever throw a good pair of *high quality plastic* sunglasses in the bushes, mister." His smile widens.

fields.Title: You: "Whip 'em out!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Whip 'em out!

fields.Title: Siileng: ""...it's beautiful. Beautiful freed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...it's beautiful. Beautiful freedom!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Yeah -- *cool* ruins," he agrees...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- *cool* ruins," he agrees. "I get to sell quality goods like these by cutting out the middlemen. *You* don't have to rebuild your house. Live in a crater! Or in a tree!" He points to a tree. "*Where* can you do that? Only here."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh yes! You got style, you got *pe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh yes! You got style, you got *personal* style. You know what you like." He surveys his consumerist kingdom with an air of satisfaction.

fields.Title: You: ""Wow what?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow what?"

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is, yes. Anyone can set up thei..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, yes. Anyone can set up their shop whenever they feel like it."

fields.Title: You: ""And *who* is your supplier, exactl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And *who* is your supplier, exactly?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Wait... *HUMANOX*, *humanitarian* a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait... *HUMANOX*, *humanitarian* aid...

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh, okay." The man stops, his face..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, okay." The man stops, his face suddenly serious. "But why, officer?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "God, a pack of Royals would taste *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: God, a pack of Royals would taste *so* good right now. Get you some of those tar-sticks, baby!

fields.Title: You: ""See this island over there?" (Poin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "See this island over there?" (Point at the sea.) "I need money to fund an expedition there. It's important for the case."

fields.Title: Drama: "It feels great."
fields.Dialogue Text: It feels great.

fields.Title: You: "(Proceed.) "We're looking for a lor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Proceed.) "We're looking for a lorry driver who is transporting drugs out of the harbour. He or she is in this traffic jam."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Okay, maybe I'm a lorry driver too..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, maybe I'm a lorry driver too -- a little. But that's not the most important thing about me, that's my day job. This is my *dream*." He spreads his arms.

fields.Title: You: ""Could she be associated with the H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could she be associated with the Hardie boys?"

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, I'm funny. This isn't a civi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I'm funny. This isn't a civil forfeiture, I just want to ask some questions."

fields.Title: Siileng: "He smiles brightly. "If you say so,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He smiles brightly. "If you say so, officer. I don't worry too much about politics. I'm an entrepreneur, you know? Whatever's good for business is good for me."

fields.Title: You: ""Where'd you get those *comfy* pant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where'd you get those *comfy* pants?"

fields.Title: You: ""Because I want you to bribe me. I'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because I want you to bribe me. I'm a police officer, remember? That's what you're supposed to *do* around here."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Sorry, detective." The man grins a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, detective." The man grins as if the entire incident is already forgotten.

fields.Title: You: ""Five reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Five reál."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "He's *aching* to get back to his us..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's *aching* to get back to his usual shtick. All this whispering is bad for business.

fields.Title: You: ""Do you have a permit to sell all t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you have a permit to sell all that?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Good joke, officer! Here we don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good joke, officer! Here we don't have permits, just economic freedom. Take a look around..." He takes a deep breath.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No need for discounts at Siileng's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No need for discounts at Siileng's, officer. Everything's already on sale." He nods towards the crates. "Anything you want, 50% off!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Then fire away, officer!" He settl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then fire away, officer!" He settles back into the pile of boxes he's sitting on, getting comfortable.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What? No. I can't believe you said..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What? No. I can't believe you said that! You got *personal* style! You know what you like."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I think that's fair." He settles b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think that's fair." He settles back into the pile of boxes he's sitting on, making himself comfortable.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's right, no permits, no burea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, no permits, no bureaucracy! That's why this city -- *and* its law officials -- are *so* cool!"

fields.Title: You: ""Then I'm protecting a state lawles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then I'm protecting a state lawlessness. I'm not an officer of law, I'm an officer of common anarchy."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Hyper cool." He nods solemnly, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hyper cool." He nods solemnly, then breathes out a sigh of pride surveying the city around him.

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's just like *bus*, or *seagull*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's just like *bus*, or *seagull* -- a kid watching out of a window describing things going by. He doesn't like it too much, but what do you do.

fields.Title: You: ""It's an investment in your custome..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an investment in your customer base. Gotta prime the pump, man!"

fields.Title: You: ""A guy told me I need money to live..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A guy told me I need money to live, otherwise it's game over -- and I don't want to die."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's even cooler -- you investig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's even cooler -- you investigating that and all. But --" he points to the goods. "I am not a lorry driver, I'm just a street vendor. I don't know anything about that."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "No. He wasn't talking about an abst..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. He wasn't talking about an abstract crowd. It was *that crowd*.

fields.Title: Empathy: "He doesn't want to talk about them...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't want to talk about them... he's *afraid*.

fields.Title: You: ""Who are these 'other drivers' who..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who are these 'other drivers' who talk?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It could be. She was strange."
fields.Dialogue Text: It could be. She was strange.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Tapes?" The notion sounds preposte..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tapes?" The notion sounds preposterous to him. "Tapes are *everywhere*! They're worthless, kids throw them in the trees -- there's one in the bushes, right behind this lorry."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's right, officer, but it's a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, officer, but it's a bad scene for business there. Too many regulations, extremely bad for an independent local entrepreneur."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Yeah, that's the main thing about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, that's the main thing about you." He nods admiringly. "Freedom is great, it's what lets independent entrepreneurs, like me, sell quality goods at competitive prices."

fields.Title: You: "Don't fret. Let him answer."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't fret. Let him answer.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Look, officer. I'm just the retail..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, officer. I'm just the retailer. You'd have to talk to my supplier if you got questions about the supply chain. That's how the game works."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""It *is* -- *practically* free. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It *is* -- *practically* free. Yours for five cents a piece! Rock that tuna -- why not some macaroni too?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""They're *very* delicious. *And* sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They're *very* delicious. *And* shelf stable. You can keep all this out in the sun come summer! Try it -- buy some tuna. Won't rot. Un-rottable."

fields.Title: Drama: "It's for show, my liege. He knows y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's for show, my liege. He knows you need more than this to bust this guy. Later, perhaps?

fields.Title: Siileng: ""It's very cool of you to ask again..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's very cool of you to ask again -- it's the third time now. How about you give *me* money and I give *you* cool pants and sneakers." He points to them.

fields.Title: You: ""Five reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Five reál."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh, okay." Siileng stops, his face..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, okay." Siileng stops, his face suddenly serious. "But why, officer?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Drugs?" For a moment he's unsure h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Drugs?" For a moment he's unsure how to respond. "I don't go in for that, officer. Drugs ruin lives."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's very cool, a lot of the coo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's very cool, a lot of the coolest detectives do drugs. Sadly, I don't have any drugs on sale -- or at my home. Or on my person." He smiles.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Crowd -- you know? The drug crowd.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Crowd -- you know? The drug crowd."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay. We're cool now." (Conclude.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. We're cool now." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: Siileng: "He nods. "In her lorry there, but....."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods. "In her lorry there, but... I don't know if it's her... Are we cool now? I think we're cool now."

fields.Title: You: ""You, I want your money. Now.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You, I want your money. Now."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Good one, officer. You're a funny..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good one, officer. You're a funny guy! Now what can I do for you?" He nods toward his shabby wares.

fields.Title: You: ""What do you think is going to happ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you think is going to happen when all those finger-bullets come raining down to earth?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Very cool," the street vendor nods..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very cool," the street vendor nods, his eyebrows furrowed, "I admire your awareness of our intertwined histories. It's super nice of you to apologize for colonialism. But the Apricot Suzerainty is a shithole -- that's why I left."

fields.Title: You: ""Man, this apricots business sounds..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Man, this apricots business sounds complicated all of a sudden."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If you wanted to be *cynical* abou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If you wanted to be *cynical* about it, you could say we're here to protect the interests of property holders. I'm not, however."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Happy shopping, officer! Everythin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Happy shopping, officer! Everything's cool here!" He gives you a thumbs up.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Interesting." The lieutenant whips..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Interesting." The lieutenant whips out his blue notebook and makes a note.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "You glance around the decrepit buil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You glance around the decrepit buildings, the miserable weather, the sidewalks strewn with sunflower seeds and the dust-choked air...

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No, no. It's very cool, officer. Y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, no. It's very cool, officer. You're a cool cop for caring about those things. You should buy cool glasses too." He points to a pile of sunglasses.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay. No permit then. Cool.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. No permit then. Cool."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "A bold move! Let's see if it pays o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A bold move! Let's see if it pays off.

fields.Title: You: ""But you *are* a lorryman. Another..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you *are* a lorryman. Another driver has identified you *and* your lorry."

fields.Title: You: ""So you admit you're a lorry driver.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you admit you're a lorry driver."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Exactly! It's such a small part of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Exactly! It's such a small part of my life. It's in the rear view mirror now. I'm climbing out of that hole -- with ingenuity."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Look..." He looks around and lower..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look..." He looks around and lowers his voice. "There's bad people doing *bad* things here -- that's all I know. Please don't get me into this mess, I've spent fifteen years working my way up..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No use -- he's not telling us. He'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No use -- he's not telling us. He's too afraid. We need to take him to my station and ask him there. *After* we've called his boss."

fields.Title: You: ""The food packages you're selling h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The food packages you're selling have *humanitarian aid* written on them. How come?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Yes, apricots come from Siigay," t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, apricots come from Siigay," the man explains. "My grandma used to grow them. But Siigay is a shithole, that's why I came to Revachol. Here's much better for an independent entrepreneur. Less *laws*."

fields.Title: Composure: "You feel a twitch in your index fin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You feel a twitch in your index fingers. There's a finger-shootout a-brewing.

fields.Title: You: ""Sorry, I didn't mean to say that...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, I didn't mean to say that. I meant to say that you're from..." (Pronounce it very painstakingly.) "... See-guy..."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Speaking of, could I convince you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Speaking of, could I convince you to support an independent local entrepreneur right now?"

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Siileng: ""*Now* we're getting somewhere," th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Now* we're getting somewhere," the street vendor nods. "If you'd only give me a good reason as well..."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "God, a pack of Royals would taste *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: God, a pack of Royals would taste *so* good right now. Get you some of those tar-sticks, baby!

fields.Title: You: ""Ten reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ten reál."

fields.Title: You: ""Because I... am corrupt? I don't r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because I... am corrupt? I don't really remember how it works, though -- being corrupt, I mean."

fields.Title: You: ""I actually *don't* like drugs.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I actually *don't* like drugs."

fields.Title: You: ""If you don't want to get into this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If you don't want to get into this mess..." (Raise your voice) "You HAVE to give us a REASON to move on."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "No need to dress this one up, just..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No need to dress this one up, just tell him what you want.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Sure, mister, very cool. Take a ni..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, mister, very cool. Take a nice long look, I've got all sorts of things here."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""*Everything's* cool. The goods are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Everything's* cool. The goods are cool, the customers are cool, the place is cool -- and one more thing, officer..."

fields.Title: You: ""Is there a discount for cool offic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is there a discount for cool officers like me?"

fields.Title: You: ""Yum. Apricots are delicious.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yum. Apricots are delicious."

fields.Title: You: ""A shakedown.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A shakedown."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "*Apricot Suzerainty* calls to mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Apricot Suzerainty* calls to mind an era when the Siigay archipelago was colonized by Revachol. It's a bit of a slur, in other words.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I would, officer, gladly, but I do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I would, officer, gladly, but I don't have any cash on hand, you know?" He winks. "But maybe if you *buy* something first *then* I'll have some money you can shake me down for. Sound fair?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not here to play with finger-p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not here to play with finger-pistols. I'm here on official business."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, but what am *I* doing here,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, but what am *I* doing here, if there are no permits?" (Stare at the police insignia on your sleeve.)
fields.Alternate1: "Wait, but what are *we* doing here, if there are no permits?" (Look at Kim and the police insignia on his sleeve.)

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's right. Revachol is the best..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right. Revachol is the best place for an independent self-employer like myself. That's why it's so *cool* with all the models coming here and cool celebrities..." He smiles his bright toothpaste-ad smile.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Hey -- why not support *this* loca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey -- why not support *this* local entrepreneur? You can start by buying a pair of sexy pants. Or cool sunglasses... maybe some macaroni?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant winces at the words..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant winces at the words -- slightly.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know why I'm talking about..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know why I'm talking about this. It's some kind of... mind-reaction." (Point to your head.)

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Officer, do I look like a drug lor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, do I look like a drug lord? I don't have that kinda money. Be reasonable here."

fields.Title: You: ""Ten reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ten reál."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Sir, it appears to be true. No drug..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sir, it appears to be true. No drugs in sight -- not in the box of sunglasses *or* under the speakers.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's cool. Especially after you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's cool. Especially after you already said you're into them. All the coolest detectives in the movies do drugs *and* are very conflicted about it. Still -- no drugs here." He smiles.

fields.Title: You: ""So you were *embarrassed* to tell..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you were *embarrassed* to tell me?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Nothing, I told you. I'm not a dum..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing, I told you. I'm not a dumb guy -- I don't get involved with that crowd. "

fields.Title: You: ""It wasn't *some drug crowd*. You k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It wasn't *some drug crowd*. You know who they are. Tell me now!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I only accept *legal* tender, offi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I only accept *legal* tender, officer." He lowers his voice. "Unless that's code for something?"

fields.Title: You: ""Hey, a quick question -- do you se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, a quick question -- do you sell any tapes?"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: IsTaskActive("TASK.find_egg_melody")  and  CheckItem("tape_melody_broken") == false  and  CheckItem("tape_melody_fixed") == false--[[ Variable[ ]]

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Ten reál is a bargain for that kin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ten reál is a bargain for that kind of investment! You got it, my man." He takes a ten-note from a leather pouch.

fields.Title: Empathy: "The air between you becomes a littl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air between you becomes a little awkward as it becomes clear you don't know the first thing about bribes.

fields.Title: You: ""One million reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "One million reál."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""Think of it as an *investment*.""]
Volition: "*Or* you could *not* make this abou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Or* you could *not* make this about corruption and go with something even wilder.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's very cool. I don't like dru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's very cool. I don't like drugs, either. I only said I do because I didn't want to sound *lame*." He smiles. "Peer pressure."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No. I just forgot. It's such a sma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I just forgot. It's such a small part of my life. It's in the rear view mirror now. I'm climbing out of that hole -- with ingenuity."

fields.Title: You: ""Could her name be *Ruby* by any ch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could her name be *Ruby* by any chance?"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Start with a little compliment, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Start with a little compliment, then work your way up from there -- this is about business, remember.

fields.Title: Shivers: "...from out on the bay a cool wind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...from out on the bay a cool wind gathers. It sweeps into the city, tugging at the textiles hanging around the stand. Some distance away the sound of a tin can clattering across the street can be heard...

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Very cool. I like your style, offi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very cool. I like your style, officer."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "There you go. A witness with corrob..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There you go. A witness with corroborating evidence: it's Ruby.

fields.Title: Drama: "A convincing performance, bravo!"
fields.Dialogue Text: A convincing performance, bravo!

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The name "Siileng" is embroidered o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The name "Siileng" is embroidered over his breast pocket.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Anything for you..." He smiles aga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anything for you..." He smiles again.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Ah, yes. Lots of cops are." The st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, yes. Lots of cops are." The street vendor nods, dead-serious.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's cool. Especially after you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's cool. Especially after you said you *don't* like them. All the cool detectives do drugs without liking them. Sadly I don't have any drugs on sale here." He smiles.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's *so* cool -- you investigat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's *so* cool -- you investigating the local drug trade like some cool Narc. But --" he points to the goods. "I am not a lorry driver, I'm just a street vendor. I don't know anything about that."

fields.Title: You: ""Siileng, my source tells me *you'r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Siileng, my source tells me *you're* the one transporting drugs for the Union."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""And what *crowd* is that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And what *crowd* is that?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Here we go. There's a *tiny bit* of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Here we go. There's a *tiny bit* of truth on the table. Zoom in on it.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""All right!" He snaps back to his a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right!" He snaps back to his act. "Very cool. Let's cap this off with a *purchase*. A pair of funky sunglasses, detective. You deserve it! And *I* deserve it too, don't you think?"
fields.Alternate1: "All right!" He snaps back to his usual self. "Ice cold. Let's cap this off with a purchase. You can walk away from here with funky sunglasses, detectives -- both of you. You deserve it!"

fields.Title: You: ""I'll look around, thanks." [Leave...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'll look around, thanks." [Leave.]
fields.Alternate1: "I'll leave you to it for now." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "No, it's a safety hazard."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it's a safety hazard.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's *so* cool, officer. Speakin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's *so* cool, officer. Speaking of, why not support an independent local entrepreneur by buying some pants and glasses?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Gossamer is a fine, filmy substance..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Gossamer is a fine, filmy substance consisting of cobwebs spun by small spiders, seen especially in autumn. It's safe to say he's referring to the near absence of regulations.

fields.Title: Volition: "Don't be distracted by the flattery..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't be distracted by the flattery and funny-man act. *Questions*.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""But officer, I don't have that kin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But officer, I don't have that kind of money. There's got to be a more modest investment."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant nods calmly and says..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant nods calmly and says: "Corruption."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""An investment?" He raises a brow,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "An investment?" He raises a brow, intrigued. "What kind of investment?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What, only a fiver? You can't even..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, only a fiver? You can't even buy a pack of Royal Extras with that -- let's make this one *stick*, my man."

fields.Title: Siileng: "He looks you straight in the eye. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He looks you straight in the eye. "I hear you, officer," he agrees. "What kind of a sum are we talking about here?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Sounds like a fair deal all around..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sounds like a fair deal all around." He takes a ten-note from a leather pouch.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I... officer," he nods. He is genu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I... officer," he nods. He is genuinely perplexed.

fields.Title: You: ""Five reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Five reál."

fields.Title: You: ""Invest into me not telling your em..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Invest into me not telling your employer about your operation here."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""So you admit you're a lorry driver?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you admit you're a lorry driver?"

fields.Title: You: ""Stop squirming. What do you know a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Stop squirming. What do you know about the drug operation at the harbour?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Okay, look..." He looks around and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, look..." He looks around and lowers his voice. "There's *bad* people here. Doing *bad* things. That's all I know. Please don't get into this mess. I've been Revachol for *fifteen* years, working my way up..."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Interesting. Could this driver be c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Interesting. Could this driver be connected to the Hardie boys?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is not code. He really means hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is not code. He really means his individual net worth," the lieutenant jumps in. "It is *not* legal tender."

fields.Title: Authority: "Even better! It's like a shakedown,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even better! It's like a shakedown, but somehow legal. This is "civil asset forfeiture."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You're threatening my inviolable p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're threatening my inviolable property rights?" He inhales dramatically, then simmers down.

fields.Title: You: ""So 'cool' guys protect businessmen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So 'cool' guys protect businessmen while everyone else lives in the ruins? I can think of cooler things."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "*Apricot Suzerainty* calls to mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Apricot Suzerainty* calls to mind an era when the Siigay archipelago was colonized by Revachol. It's a bit of a slur, in other words.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Of course. Fire away!" He settles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course. Fire away!" He settles back into the pile of boxes he's sitting on, making himself comfortable.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I'm an entrepreneur, officer!" He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm an entrepreneur, officer!" He begins counting on his fingers. "I've got sources, buyers, suppliers, distributors, manufacturers, wholesalers... all extremely cool and aboveboard."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "As if you've committed some faux pa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As if you've committed some faux pas.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know, it was just the only..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know, it was just the only thing I could come up with in my head -- to ask you. I need to get money *somehow*."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You see, I'm an honest entrepreneu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You see, I'm an honest entrepreneur. I can't help you if you don't give me a good reason as to why I should -- sorry, detective." The man grins as if the entire incident is already forgotten.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Hah -- that! You drive a hard barg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hah -- that! You drive a hard bargain, officer. I respect that." He nods. "Okay, what's it going to cost me? Be reasonable..."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""*Who* said that? It's the fat raci..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Who* said that? It's the fat racist, right? I bet it's him. He has an agenda against me, because I'm an immigrant who works harder than he does. He's a hater."

fields.Title: You: ""You're wasting my time. Tell me wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're wasting my time. Tell me who the *fuck* is transporting the drugs here!"

fields.Title: You: ""Is the lady driver the old woman b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is the lady driver the old woman back there?" (Point to the Paledriver.) "Dazed out, *strange*?"

fields.Title: You: ""Really? You think I'm cool?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Really? You think I'm cool?"

fields.Title: You: ""Whether I'm cool is unimportant, I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whether I'm cool is unimportant, I have *police* questions for you."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant nods approvingly."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant nods approvingly.

fields.Title: You: ""I think one said 'Not for Resale'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think one said 'Not for Resale' on the packaging."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Yeah, Revachol's the coolest. Does..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, Revachol's the coolest. Doesn't care about where you're from, who you are... It's all about *freedom*." He nods admiringly.

fields.Title: Logic: "Yes. It's a business secret. Let hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. It's a business secret. Let him keep it.

fields.Title: You: ""Think of it as an *investment*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Think of it as an *investment*."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What, only a fiver? You can't even..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, only a fiver? You can't even buy a pack of Royal Extras with that -- let's make this one *stick*, my friend!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""But officer, bribe you to do what?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But officer, bribe you to do what?" The street vendor's expression is dead serious.

fields.Title: You: ""You said I was a cool cop, but it'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You said I was a cool cop, but it's not very cool to freeze to death on a cold park bench."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm super into drugs.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm super into drugs."

fields.Title: You: ""We're buddies, Siileng. Help us ou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're buddies, Siileng. Help us out. No one will know it was you."

fields.Title: Logic: "But did he first mark them up 100%,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But did he first mark them up 100%, just so he could put them on "sale"?

fields.Title: Siileng: ""My man, you know how the game is p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My man, you know how the game is played! You and me, we should work together. What do you think -- shake things up?" He winks.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What, no finger-pistols, officer?"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, no finger-pistols, officer?" The street vendor makes a little *pew-pew* sound.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You're right, officer, 100%." He r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right, officer, 100%." He returns his finger-pistols to their finger-holsters. "No playing around then. Strictly business. Maybe I can interest you in some premium menswear instead?"
fields.Alternate1: "You're right, officer, 100%." He adjusts his shirt collar. "No playing around then. Strictly business. Maybe I can interest you in some premium menswear instead?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not cool.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not cool."

fields.Title: Siileng: "You see a Samaran street vendor sur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see a Samaran street vendor surrounded by a motley assemblage of goods. When he realizes you're looking at him his face breaks into a wide welcoming grin...

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "No hassle? There's a *little* of a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No hassle? There's a *little* of a hassle here, it appears. A moral hassle.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Are you trying to ask for a *bribe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you trying to ask for a *bribe*? If so, you're not doing a very good job..." He looks at the vendor.

fields.Title: You: ""One million reál.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "One million reál."

fields.Title: You: ""So, Siileng -- what's *your* stanc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, Siileng -- what's *your* stance on drugs?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "There's more here. He's *afraid* of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's more here. He's *afraid* of this crowd, whoever they are. More than he is of the racist lorryman.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The third driver," he nods. "We ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The third driver," he nods. "We haven't talked to her yet. Where exactly is she -- near the horseback monument?"

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He's not ruling her out."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's not ruling her out.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Everything's still cool here, offi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Everything's still cool here, officer," the street vendor assures you.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "This man probably comes from Siigay..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This man probably comes from Siigay, sometimes known as the 'Apricot Suzerainty,' an archipelago in the Samaran isola.

fields.Title: You: "(Better not to mention.) "Sounds go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Better not to mention.) "Sounds good. Let's get back to business then."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Well. If it's for his *grandma*......"
fields.Dialogue Text: Well. If it's for his *grandma*... you should buy a lot of things.

fields.Title: You: ""An arrest.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "An arrest."

fields.Title: You: ""Are those things really on sale or..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are those things really on sale or did you just jack up the price first?"

fields.Title: You: ""A gossamer state? You're right, th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A gossamer state? You're right, this *is* cool. I'm part of a hip, thin, almost non-existent state apparatus!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""My man, officer, *you* make all th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My man, officer, *you* make all this possible! Without you, this climate would be extremely bad for business. You're part of the gossamer state!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Wow.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow."

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, is it true? He doesn't need a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, is it true? He doesn't need a permit to sell?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He does not need your money. Pleas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He does not need your money. Please disregard that. We're just here to ask some questions."

fields.Title: You: ""That's all then. Let me ask you so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all then. Let me ask you something else."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Somewhere not so distant, officer C..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somewhere not so distant, officer Chad Tillbrook refuses a bribe from a local hood. He doesn't know you've just made his job, and the job of all honest cops, a little bit harder.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Because you need to solve the bigge..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because you need to solve the biggest case in the history of criminal sciences.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Wow! So cool... you keep saying *t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow! So cool... you keep saying *the same sentence*, mister. No difference. Same words." He grins in amazement. "Let me donate you some sunglasses. For only 20 cents to 2 reál."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "God, a pack of Royals would taste *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: God, a pack of Royals would taste *so* good right now. Get you some of those tar-sticks, baby!

fields.Title: You: ""It's an investment in me, a highly..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's an investment in me, a highly experimental human being. My risk/reward ratio is insane."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No. That's insane... It's the fat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. That's insane... It's the fat hater! He's been eyeing me for a week and he sent you here. Maybe *he's* the one, huh? Have you thought about that?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Speaking of -- why not support an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Speaking of -- why not support an independent local entrepreneur? I send half my profits back to my grandma in Siigay."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Very cool," Siileng nods, his eyeb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very cool," Siileng nods, his eyebrows furrowed, "I admire your awareness of our intertwined histories. It's super nice of you to apologize for colonialism. But the Apricot Suzerainty is a shithole -- that's why I left."

fields.Title: You: ""You're welcome. I do try to be sup..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're welcome. I do try to be supportive of other peoples and cultures."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Good joke, officer, you're very fu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good joke, officer, you're very funny, you know that?"

fields.Title: You: ""I'm a policeman. It's an investmen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm a policeman. It's an investment in good relations with the RCM."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What, only a fiver? You can't even..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, only a fiver? You can't even buy a pack of Royal Extras with that -- let's make this one *stick*, my man."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Unless *you're* into drugs, of cou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Unless *you're* into drugs, of course -- in which case, drugs are *excellent*." He kisses his fingers. "Tasty-tasty drugs."

fields.Title: You: ""So you *forgot* to tell me?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you *forgot* to tell me?"

fields.Title: You: ""She? Where is she? I haven't yet m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "She? Where is she? I haven't yet met a woman on the roundabout."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I don't know. I told you... I don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know. I told you... I don't know her name."

fields.Title: You: ""Do you accept net worth as a form..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you accept net worth as a form of payment?"

fields.Title: You: ""What's so cool?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's so cool?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Very sharp, officer. I'm Seraise,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Very sharp, officer. I'm Seraise, from the Siigay province of the Seraise Empire. The 'Apricot Suzerainty', you know?"

fields.Title: You: ""Even better, it's civil asset forf..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Even better, it's civil asset forfeiture." (Make an imaginary warning shot.)

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You like premium menswear! Look ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You like premium menswear! Look around and browse, everything looks cool on a guy like you. Take your time." He settles back into the pile of boxes he's sitting on.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Only the coolest goods in Revachol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Only the coolest goods in Revachol. I've got sneakers, speakers, *extremely* comfy pants too. Try them on right here. No shame -- only freedom."

fields.Title: You: ""Does your supplier drive that HUMA..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Does your supplier drive that HUMANOX lorry over there?" (Point at the lorry with the big HUMANOX sign on it.)

fields.Title: Siileng: ""What?" The street vendor looks ove..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What?" The street vendor looks over his left shoulder and stares at the lorry -- as though he's never seen a lorry in his entire life.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, well -- if they're delicious..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, well -- if they're delicious it's okay."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Tugging at his heart strings like t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tugging at his heart strings like that... doesn't it feel a bit manipulative?

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Okay, officer," he finally says, "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, officer," he finally says, "I can't leave a man in need like that. How much do you need?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't think you really understan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think you really understand how bribes work, detective..." He looks at you, then the vendor.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I guess it can't be any riskier th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess it can't be any riskier than speculating in exotic derivatives... how much are we talking about here?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "To the west, dark brown ribbons of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To the west, dark brown ribbons of tape hang from the tree, flowing in the wind...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You should have a look. It's better..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should have a look. It's better than nothing.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""In that case, I cannot accept that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In that case, I cannot accept that as payment, officer. I run everything above board here. Cash only."

fields.Title: You: ""But you're not a local, are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you're not a local, are you?"

fields.Title: You: ""Sweet, no permits means less work..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sweet, no permits means less work for me. Let's move on."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No problem here, officer. I get al..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No problem here, officer. I get all this from one of my suppliers, an extremely reputable guy."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You mean these *delicious* pre-pac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mean these *delicious* pre-packaged, shelf-stable meal kits? Really easy to cook, no hassle, *really* cheap too -- buy some, try them out!"

fields.Title: You: ""Don't play games with me, hawker...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't play games with me, hawker. What's going on?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh, he's a good guy. I think you'd..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, he's a good guy. I think you'd get along. I'll let you know the next time he's around."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, is it really true that you d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, is it really true that you don't need a *single permit* to set up a shop?"
